title\": \"Shatter the Glass and Salt the Whisper\", \"text\": \"You stop at the cracked conduit and feel the pulse like a warning bell under your thumbs, a rhythm you do not trust to be led by any hand but a tide-priest’s. The packet calls to you with a sweet little lie about being only a prayer, and you answer with discipline learned on the Skyhook: you put it against stone and press until the saint-glass sings into pieces. Shards glitter in the dim like trapped stars, and you gather them in your buckler and sprinkle salt from your belt pouch, a fisher’s ward to weigh down reckless wishes. The taste of brine and glass dust is sharp as a lesson, and the Engine’s hum settles, as if pleased that an itch was not scratched. You scatter the salted grit into the leak-mist and watch it vanish as if swallowed by a satisfied throat, then you turn back up the rung with your shoulders squared to meet consequences you now own.\", \"outcome\": \"Keth’s eyes cool to pearl-gray when you report, and his grin becomes the paper-thin edge of a knife; the favor he promised stays promised, but he changes the tense like a miser with a broken abacus and says that not all coins are minted in the same season. You still win quiet thanks from quarters that do not stamp gratitude into clay—temple whispers soften around your name, and a Tidemother acolyte leaves a braid of river grass at your door like a blessing that refuses to speak. The hidden rung remains a path in your mind, and you step through Warden nets with ease born of practice and the knowledge of where the city bends away from watchlight. Yet a lookout’s rumor grows teeth and nips at your heels; the Black Net begins to weigh you as a liability with sharp potential, and you see more left hands brush knife-hilts when you pass. When the rains come, your mother’s brace still aches, and you feel every flinch like a debt that multiplied in the dark, even as you like yourself better when you meet your reflection in saint-glass.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C3\", \"title\": \"Etch a New Rhythm with the Stormglass\", \"text\": \"You set the packet against your knee and listen to the Engine’s hum until your bones remember their old habit of counting beats without numbers, just distance and need. The stormglass whistle at your throat cools, then warms, answering a pressure change that only you and the Skyhook swifts seem to care about, and you take a shard from its leather sleeve. Scratching counter-melody into saint-glass is like plucking thunder with a fishbone pick; it wants to leap from your hand, but you guide it with pilot’s patience and Warden stubbornness. You etch a notch, then two, rewriting a cadence so the whisper will lead not to a drowned vault the size of a basilica but to a lesser sluice, a gate meant for floods to be bled safely without waking the city’s deeper sleep. When the new pattern is cut, you press the glass to the conduit and let the leak-mist kiss it into the dark, then you place a palm to bone and promise the long body of the leviathan that you will ask before you sing again.\", \"outcome\": \"Something below answers, not with the groan of a titan but with the relieved sigh of a narrow hinge long rusted; a lesser water gate stirs and then stills, its name written in you as surely as in stone. You return with the certainty of a navigator who has charted a new channel, and you copy the revised pulse onto oiled vellum and into memory, a secret you will spend only once because the city allows no second plucking of the same chord. Keth honors the letter of his promise because your hands did the work, even if your song was not the one he sent; he wipes a ledger clean where it matters most and pretends not to notice how you did it, though his eyes take the measure of your audacity with grudging admiration. The hidden rung becomes more than a path: it becomes a route whose ending you own, a bypass that will carry you past a Warden checkpoint like a ghost when you must fly without wake. For days after, the Engine’s hum matches your heartbeat when you pass the sternum’s great braces, and you understand, with a thrill and a warning, that you now carry a key whose teeth fit only one lock and whose breakage would be a sin and a salvation all at once.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C4\", \"title\": \"Spin the Lookout and Scrub the Trail\", \"text\": \"When the lookout slides from eel-glow and shadow like a knife drawn from a sleeve, you greet him with the tired familiarity of a city that taught you three languages of threat and two of mercy. You talk of false schedules and decoy couriers, of tax songs sung out of key to draw nets away, and you lace each lie with a truth heavy enough to keep the blend from floating. Your Saint-Glass Buckler throws soft green light into his eyes at moments you choose, buying you heartbeats to lay false footprints in the dew of leak-mist and to brush away the true with a fisher’s gentle patience. You leave a scrap of cloth that belonged to a Warden quartermaster you know is on leave, and you hum a river tune that smugglers avoid, a hymn that says warded, warded, warded in the mouths of frogs and the turn of reeds. By the time you slip past, the lookout is arguing with his own suspicions, and your trail is so clean that even you could not swear you walked it.\", \"outcome\": \"The Black Net’s rumor mill grinds for nothing when it tries to spit out your route; three different accounts place you in three different ribs, and Keth’s ledgers shake off your footprints like a dog shedding river water. Wardens grumble at a false trail that leads them to a harmless rung capped with wax older than their promotions, and your old patrol finds nothing to stain the memory of the badge you still wear as a pendant. Keth is frustrated, but he cannot scold success without looking like a fool to his own, so he pays the debt with visible reluctance and invisible interest you can taste but not measure. Your map of hidden paths grows, and the rung you walked becomes part of your inner city, a place you can go with your eyes shut and your body listening. Later, when storms close the Nine Mouths and the Ferryman’s token chills against your skin, you will thank this night for teaching you how to pass like fog over eel-slick bone without leaving even a whisper behind.\"}\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"2\"], \"next\": [\"4\", \"9\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"favor\", \"description\": \"A promise from Keth that removes your name from one smuggler ledger, cutting a knot from the line that has trailed you since the Bazaar learned your debts.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"knowledge\", \"description\": \"Knowledge of a hidden rung path that bypasses a Warden checkpoint, memorized in bends of bone and pools of shadow rather than ink and chart.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"arcane pattern\", \"description\": \"If the packet is altered: a revised pulse pattern that can open a lesser water gate once, a single-use rhythm etched in memory like a chord plucked from the Skyhook.\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"